enu zDocsDropdownMenu\"><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportTopicButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"singlePdf\" role=\"button\">Save selected topic</a><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportSubtopicsButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"pdfWithChildren\" role=\"button\">Save selected topic and subtopics</a><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportBundleButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"wholeBundlePdf\" role=\"button\">Save entire publication</a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicShare zDocsShareButton\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-expanded=\"false\" aria-label=\"Share\" class=\"d-none d-lg-flex zDocsShareDialogButton\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" data-tooltip-content=\"Share\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-share\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-share\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none zDocsShareDialogButton\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-share\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-share\"></use></svg>Share</span><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu\"><a class=\"dropdown-item zDocsShareButton zDocsShareEmail\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\"><span>Email Link</span></a><a class=\"dropdown-item zDocsShareButton zDocsShareLink\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\"><span>Copy Link</span></a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsFeedback zDocsFeedback zDocsTopicFeedback\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-label=\"Feedback\" class=\"zDocsFeedbackButton d-none d-lg-flex\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_3612790\" data-toggle=\"modal\" data-tooltip-content=\"Feedback\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none d-flex zDocsFeedbackButton\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-return-focus=\"#zDocsTopicActionsMobile\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_3612790\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Sept 13, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104eji1665703130687.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/eji1665703130687.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/eji1665703130687.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"eji1665703130687\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      trigger option\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body refbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Trigger for handling the processing that should occur after a menu item is selected.\n </p>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"eji1665703130687__section_w2912ab1b7b1_w2913ab1b7_w2914ab1\">\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"2\" id=\"eji1665703130687__table_d14669e1_d14670e1_d14671e1\"><caption></caption><colgroup><col/><col/></colgroup><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\"> Declaration: </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">trigger option</code>\n</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\"> Applies to: </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\"> Menu Item </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\"> Activation: </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\"> Activated when a user selects the item from a\n                        menu. </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\"> Default behavior: </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\"> None </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\"> Behavior upon completion: </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\"> None </td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"eji1665703130687__section_w2915ab1b7b3_w2916ab1b7_w2917ab1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d146768e123\"> Description </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"eji1665703130687__p_d117992e1_d117993e1_d117994e1\">The ProcScript in the option trigger determines\n            what happens when the menu item is selected. This code operates on the currently active\n            form, even if the menu item belongs to another (inactive) form. As such, the ProcScript\n            in an option trigger can be seen as an extension of the code in the currently active\n            form; ProcScript functions such as <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$instancename</span>,\n               <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$totocc</span>, and so on, return the values for that form.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"eji1665703130687__p_d117995e1_d117996e1_d117997e1\">Menu items usually define shortcuts; for example,\n            they may be provided to ^RETRIEVE data, to ^STORE data, to ^QUIT a form, or to ^ACCEPT a\n            form. This functionality is usually provided by way of the <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">macro</span>\n            statement.</p>\n<div class=\"note note note_note\" id=\"eji1665703130687__note_w2924ab1b7b3b7_w2925ab1b7b3_w2926ab1b7_w2927ab1\"><span class=\"note__title\">Note:</span> You can\n            reference global ProcScript and variables from the current library in the option trigger\n            but you cannot directly access local functions.</div>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"eji1665703130687__section_w2918ab1b7b5_w2919ab1b7_w2920ab1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d146768e147\"> Processing Dynamic Menu Items </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"eji1665703130687__p_d118001e1_d118002e1_d118003e1\">Dynamic menus have only one option trigger, no\n            matter how many menu items they actually contain. The option trigger must therefore be\n            able to process each menu item in the dynamic menu. To do so, it takes an input\n            parameter of data type String, which contains the identifier of the selected menu item.\n            The following code is typical for the option trigger of a dynamic menu:</p>\n<div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">;Option trigger\nparams\n String strId : in\nendparams\n;Obtain the id of selected menu item and perform the associated action \n selectcase strId\n &lt;do action&gt;\n endselectcase\nend; select</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n<div class=\"div\">\n<p class=\"p\">For example, the following code displays a message indicating which\n               menu item has been selected:</p>\n<div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">;Option trigger\nparams\n String strId\nendparams\n;Obtain the id of selected menu item and perform the associated action \n selectcase strId\n case \"MyId1\"\n message/info \"Option A selected\"\n case \"MyId2\"\n message/info \"Option B selected\"\n endcase\nend; select</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n</div>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/ckm1665702665911.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>trigger preDisplay</a><p>System trigger that is executed before a menu or menu item is displayed.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/nvc1705580311070.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Define and Use Menus</a><p>You can define menu bars, context menus, drop-down menus, and dynamic menus for the application as a whole or for individual form components. Menus are defined and deployed in libraries.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_3612790\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_3612790\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "trigger option Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Sept 13, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 trigger option Trigger for handling the processing that should occur after a menu item is selected. Declaration: trigger option Applies to: Menu Item Activation: Activated when a user selects the item from a menu. Default behavior: None Behavior upon completion: None Description The ProcScript in the option trigger determines what happens when the menu item is selected. This code operates on the currently active form, even if the menu item belongs to another (inactive) form. As such, the ProcScript in an option trigger can be seen as an extension of the code in the currently active form; ProcScript functions such as $instancename , $totocc , and so on, return the values for that form. Menu items usually define shortcuts; for example, they may be provided to ^RETRIEVE data, to ^STORE data, to ^QUIT a form, or to ^ACCEPT a form. This functionality is usually provided by way of the macro statement. Note: You can reference global ProcScript and variables from the current library in the option trigger but you cannot directly access local functions. Processing Dynamic Menu Items Dynamic menus have only one option trigger, no matter how many menu items they actually contain. The option trigger must therefore be able to process each menu item in the dynamic menu. To do so, it takes an input parameter of data type String, which contains the identifier of the selected menu item. The following code is typical for the option trigger of a dynamic menu: ;Option trigger params String strId : in endparams ;Obtain the id of selected menu item and perform the associated action selectcase strId <do action> endselectcase end; select Copy For example, the following code displays a message indicating which menu item has been selected: ;Option trigger params String strId endparams ;Obtain the id of selected menu item and perform the associated action selectcase strId case \"MyId1\" message/info \"Option A selected\" case \"MyId2\" message/info \"Option B selected\" endcase end; select Copy Related Links trigger preDisplay System trigger that is executed before a menu or menu item is displayed. Define and Use Menus You can define menu bars, context menus, drop-down menus, and dynamic menus for the application as a whole or for individual form components. Menus are defined and deployed in libraries. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}